It seems like it's going to be

00:43:08.742 --> 00:43:13.420
a complete transference of
power, and it's a transfer that

00:43:13.420 --> 00:43:16.539
will hold until at the end of
time.

00:43:16.539 --> 00:43:19.457
There will no longer even be a
difference presumably between

00:43:19.457 --> 00:43:24.318
the Father and the Son because,
as the Father says at line 341,

00:43:24.318 --> 00:43:28.086
"God shall be All in All."
There will be no power

00:43:28.086 --> 00:43:30.519
differential whatsoever between
the Father and the Son,

00:43:30.519 --> 00:43:35.282
and presumably there'll be no
power differential between or

00:43:35.282 --> 00:43:39.791
among any of us.
We'll all be joined at the end

00:43:39.791 --> 00:43:45.348
of time in one massive liberal,
nonhierarchical state of

00:43:45.348 --> 00:43:48.574
harmony.
The image of the "All in All"

00:43:48.574 --> 00:43:51.855
is Milton's most exuberant
visionary endpoint,

00:43:51.855 --> 00:43:55.355
and it satisfies,
I think, a lot of Milton's most

00:43:55.355 --> 00:43:58.826
liberal impulses.
Even the authoritarian

00:43:58.826 --> 00:44:03.748
structure of heaven -- and of
course, Milton's heaven is as

00:44:03.748 --> 00:44:08.925
authoritarian as any heaven has
ever been conceived -- even it

00:44:08.925 --> 00:44:13.253
will be transformed into
something like a fantasy of

00:44:13.253 --> 00:44:18.699
egalitarianism,
a fantasy of absolute equality.

00:44:18.699 --> 00:44:22.617
This ecstatic redistribution of
power and glory at the end of

00:44:22.617 --> 00:44:26.796
time can only come about because
the Son has willingly humiliated

00:44:26.796 --> 00:44:29.669
himself.
He subjects himself to the

00:44:29.669 --> 00:44:33.849
Father's wrath.I think we
recognize this gesture,

00:44:33.849 --> 00:44:38.349
